Re: Prior Authorization DENIED
Authorization Number: {{auth_id}}
Member ID: {{member_id}}

Dear {{member_name}},

After clinical review, your prior authorization request has been DENIED.

DENIED SERVICE
Service: {{service_description}}
Provider: {{provider_name}}

REASON FOR DENIAL
{{denial_reason}}

This decision was made by {{reviewer_name}} based on clinical guidelines and your plan's coverage criteria.

YOUR RIGHT TO APPEAL
You or your provider may appeal this decision:
- Standard Appeal: Submit within 180 days. Decision within 30 calendar days.
- Expedited Appeal: If medically urgent, call 1-800-555-PLAN for 72-hour review.
- External Review: Available after internal appeal is exhausted.

TO FILE AN APPEAL
Include: Authorization number, reason you disagree, and any supporting clinical documentation.
Mail to: Appeals Department, PO Box 12345, Processing Center, ST 00000
Fax: 1-800-555-FAX1

Sincerely,
Utilization Management Department

